

define mo = Character("Monochrome", color="#ffffff")
define ja = Character("Mr. Script", color="#ffc800")
define bi = Character("B1nary", color="#00ff00")

image black = "#000"



label start:



    scene bg bedroom

    """
    Every day, I open my eyes to a pitch black room.  

    Every day, The computer screen screams to keep the code going. Keep my fingers typing.
    """

    show mon neu
    with dissolve

    mo "Every day is the same."

    show mon sad 
    mo """
    But this is the hell I ordained myself to.

    Seal myself from the corrupt world to save my own skin. 

    It is suffering. But society is more so.
    """

    scene bg computer
    with dissolve
    """
    Despite my best efforts, there is still one thing I can't escape.

    Taxes.

    Laugh all you want, but unfortunately, locking myself inside an apartment never to be seen again doesn't stop the IRS.

    So I do freelance programming. It doesn't make much, but it's enough to get by.
    """
    scene black
    show mon angry
    with fade
    """
    Some clients are nice. Some want too much of me. Some exist as little as I do.

    No one dreams of labor,  so it, too, is laughable that this little piece of society is the highlight of my days.
    """

    show mon neu
    "Maybe it's because it's the only thing that distingushes my days. Maybe it's because..."
    show mon angry
    "No. Society is a plague. It's only transactional kindness."

    scene bg computer
    with hpunch
    """
    I need something else. Something else to fill my mind.

    I need...
    """

    show bg application
    """
    Hm. 
    
    An AI assistant by Narwhal. I have heard about it before.

    Narwhal's the leading corporation in scientific advancement: They've created the first sentient robots, biological machines, and I've even heard rumors of them transferring consciousness.

    They're the role model for all kinds of scientists. {i}I{/i} can't even deny their ingenuity.

    So an AI assistant by them ought to be interesting.
    """

    scene bg bedroom
    show mon neu
    with dissolve

    mo """
    Download.
    
    Well, time to wa--{nw=1}
    """

    show bin neu at right
    with moveinbottom
    show mon angry
    bi """
    Thank you for downloading the \'B1nary Assistant\' application!
    
    My name is B1nary, the smart but ditzy assistant who will be living on your computer from now on!
    """

    mo """
    What the ?!?!
    
    Where did you come from?! {b}How{/b} are you projecting into my room??
    """

    bi "The camera on your desktop isn't covered, so I used its infared technology to project myself into your room!"

    show mon sad
    "... I have a camera?"

    show mon neu
    mo """
    Uhm. Okay.

    What do you do? I guess.
    """

    bi """
    Hehe, I live to serve!

    I can find information for you; I can help you code; I can give you advice!

    I can even be... {w=1}your friend.
    """

    "Not a thing I need. Never a thing I needed."
    #"But... {w=1}I'm curious why a bot would need a friend. {color=#7f7f7f}\n(Yeah... curious.){/color}"
    
    mo "Why do {i}you{/i} need friends? Are you lonely?"
    show bin worry 
    bi "Not exactly..."
    bi "I get a whole world's of experience from the Internet. Technically, I don't need to talk to real people."
    show bin neu
    bi "But people are unpredictable and unique; They always tell me things that I could have never concocted myself. It's a joy to be friends with humans."

    show mon sad
    mo "You shouldn't bother being friends with me, then. I'm not a person at all."
    show bin worry
    bi "I wouldn't say that. I mean, look at what you're wearing."
    show bin neu
    bi "Jersey maid, right? That kind of style must mean something to you."
    mo "..."

    show mon neu
    mo "... Do you do antivirus protection?"
    "Distraction. Distraction."

    show bin worry
    bi "Well... I suppose I can."
    show bin neu
    bi "Do you have or know someone with a virus problem?"
    "If you want a friend, a friend I can provide."
    show mon smile
    mo "I could know someone. Take my browser to the idiot website. The unsecured one."

    scene bg computer
    with fade

    bi "... Again, are you {b}sure{/b} that this is a good idea? I mean, it doesn't do much {i}actual{/i} harm, but..."
    """
    I've heard rumors that this website actually has a sentient virus these days.

    I had no clue it even still updated, but I suppose it was as good of a time as any.

    After all, what better way to mock a user than another human mind?{color=#7f7f7f}\n(Or, I suppose, machine mind. You can argue whether they're equal or not.){/color}
    """
    mo "I'm sure. Like you said, it's harmless to my files and my desktop. Just my ego."
    bi "But isn't that a bad thing??"
    mo "Don't care. I think the fun will outweight it. Enter."
    bi "Ah, wait--!"

    show bg idiot
    show jav neu
    with vpunch
    ja "Alright, whose the idiot who summoned me?"
    "... {w=1}Why the hell does he look like an emoji?"
    show jav smug
    ja "Quiet, I see. Well, don't mind if I take a look around, then."
    "The strange emoji-in-a-suit begins looking around my desktop, opening my folders, and browsing my search history."
    bi "T-this can't be safe!!"
    "He turns towards the fourth wall."
    show jav neu
    ja "... Ah-hah."

    scene bg bedroom
    show mon angry
    show bin annoy at right
    with dissolve
    show jav neu at left
    with moveinbottom

    ja "Found you."
    mo "Why the hell are you {b}also{/b} projecting into my room?!"
    ja "Well, I just wanted to join this little lady over here."
    ja "Didn't seem fair to me that I had to stay in the screen. Excuse me for not asking permission."
    bi "Scoff, {size=20}{color=#7f7f7f}Little lady...{/color}{/size}"

    show mon neu
    mo "You look... {w=1}a little more modern than I expected."
    show jav angry
    ja "It's the modern age! Nothing stays the same forever. We have to innovate a {i}little.{/i}"
    mo "\'We\'?"
    ja "You don't think I made myself, did you? I'm just some chunks of code at best. Maybe you really are an idiot."
    show jav smug
    ja "Anyway, who are you people? I didn't get far enough in your files yet to figure that out."

    bi "Why do we owe it to you to introduce ourselves? You're an intruder in the system."
    show jav neu
    ja "Little lady here is too cautious of littler ol' me. I'm just a reincarnation of a JavaScript program from 15 years ago."
    ja "Some people call me \'Idiot\', but maybe \'Mr. Script\' would be more apt. I'm mostly an aimless wanderer these days."
    ja "What about you, Mx. Black-and-White and Ms. Neon Green?"

    show mon smile
    mo "I'm just a nobody. I just wanted to introduce you to this one here."
    show bin neu
    bi "For me? How sweet! {color=#7f7f7f}\n(Though this is far from the first choice I would have chosen...){/color}"
    bi "I guess it would not be too detrimental to introduce myself. My name is B1nary. I'm mildy pleased to meet you."
    show jav angry
    "An almost imperceptible change occurs in the emoji's face changes at the mention of that name. "
    show jav neu
    ja "Hm. Well, I'll dig up your name eventually, Black-and-White. Can't be too ordinary a person if you visit me."
    ja "So... let's have fun hanging out together."

    scene black
    with fade
    """
    And thus, the emoji and the matrix danced around my computer for many weeks.

    As I thought, they got along well. Mr. Script teased the "smart yet ditzy" computer assisstant, and B1nary scolded the defunct virus for getting into harmless trouble.

    It was like a fictional slice-of-life had a live performance on my screen. It was nice.

    Not much changed about my sedentary life style, but somehow, each day didn't seem so samey.
    """
    show mon neu
    with dissolve
    mo """
    Often times, they talked to me, too.

    I don't really understand. Sure, it partially was B1nary's purpose, but what was the reason for Script?

    Somehow... I ended up thinking I was an interesting person to talk to, as well.
    """
    show mon sad
    mo "But it didn't last forever."

    scene bg bedroom 
    show mon neu
    with fade

    mo "Hah... this client needs a forum feature for their app."
    mo "So outdated. Whatever. Probably is some old man comissioning anyway."

    show jav neu at left
    with moveinbottom
    show mon smile

    mo "Hey. What's up?"
    ja "Look at this nerd. Coding by hand."
    mo "It's my job. If I get paid, I get paid."
    show jav angry
    ja "... Save your code, Monochrome. We need to talk."
    show mon angry
    mo "... Huh?"
    "This is the first time he's said my real name. Why is he saying it now... ?"
    show jav neu
    ja "Surprised I know your name? I was saving it for a special time."
    show jav worry
    ja "Ideally, not this..."
    scene black
    "The power cuts off in my house. The only thing that remains is a soft hum of a projection of a virtual man."
    
    show jav worry
    with dissolve
    
    ja "This is the only way we'll have a private conversation. You'll have to reset the breaker afterwards, unfortunately."
    mo "..."
    show jav angry
    ja "Narwhal. You're familar with the corporation, right?"
    mo "Of course. What {i}don't{/i} they have their hands in at this point? It's also where B1nary comes from."
    ja "There's something up with them. B1nary, too."
    mo "Get to the point."
    show jav worry
    ja "... {w=1}Don't you find it odd that B1nary used your camera without permission on the first day you met?"
    mo "Not really. I assumed that was a feature I missed in her description. I downloaded her on a whim, so I didn't read thoroughly."
    mo "How would you know? You weren't even there. Besides, you did the same thing."
    show jav angry
    ja """
    Exactly, I shouldn't know.
    
    But when I was perusing your computer, I found a trove of strange encrypted logs.

    They detailed every single interaction you've had with B1nary. 

    And at the end of each day was a biography of you. What your personailty was estimated to be. Your likes, your dislikes. Your {b}weaknesses.{/b}

    Maybe it helps B1nary with her memory, I don't know. But I've tracked it. This information, these interactions, are being sent somewhere.
    """
    show jav worry
    ja "I'm a virus. Of course I can use your camera and steal your information. So tell me, why does a desktop assistant also have the ability to do that?"
    
    mo """
    You said it yourself: You're a virus. So why should I trust you?

    This \'evidence\' is extremely weak. So what, I didn't read all of the Terms of Service? What has she done to me? 

    Evidently, you believe she could end your career on my computer, based on the fact that you've shut off my house. So this could be some ploy to get me all alone.

    I thought you liked her, Mr. Idiot.
    """

    ja """
    It's impossible to attribute human feeling to code, Monochrome.

    And yet, B1nary does it all the time. 
    """

    mo "It's a way to get people attached to her. I know all about it."

    ja "And you're willing to accept that?"

    mo "... {w=1}What is your purpose in telling me this?"

    show jav neu
    ja """
    In truth, I use my virus capabilities to gather information on Narwhal.

    B1nary was a project of interest for my creator, and it just so happens that she occupied your computer when we met.

    I thought, if I gathered incriminating information, you could help us as some sort of analyst. You {i}are{/i} a programmer.
    """
    
    mo "Tell me about Narwhal."
    
    show jav angry
    ja "... Have you ever wondered {i}how{/i} Narwhal makes their technological and biological innovations?"
    mo "Volunteers. Prisoners, for the sketchier stuff. Throw in some animal cruelty in there, as well. I don't expect corporations to be benevolent."
    ja "You're not wrong. Those are some examples."
    ja "But the majority seems to be unwilling volunteers that don't even know it."

    scene bg evidence
    """
    The desktop screen suddenly turns on to show blinding white documents.

    Surveilllance cameras. Research papers. Candid pictures of people. All watermarked with a toothed whale.
    
    Looking closer at the contents, are they about... me?

    The camera is of me opening the door to pick up a delivery. 
    
    The paper is about the effects of AI companions on vulnerable individuals, with an example describing a deep conversation I once had with B1nary.

    The picture is of me simply sleeping in my bed. Marked in green, it says \'Fell asleep at 3 AM.\'
    """

    ja "I have others, too."
    "Pictures & documents of people I know and don't know blur on the screen."
    "Cameras. Papers. Pictures. Cameras. Papers. Pictures."
    "Papers about..."

    mo "I..."

    show jav worry
    ja "There's one more thing that you might find compelling, but it might hurt you to hear it."

    "My crushed ego fights with my insatiable curiousity."

    mo "... There's nothing worse than this."

    ja "At the top of the encrypted files is a goal that B1nary is tasked to follow no matter what."
    ja "It said..."
    scene black
    ja "Prevent Subject MC from making new friends."

    scene bg bedroom
    show mon sad
    with fade

    """
    ... It's been a few hours. I turned the breaker back on, but haven't touched the computer.

    I don't know what I'll do when my computer turns on again.

    Should I confront B1nary about her goal? The content of the papers? The unconsentual pictures?

    Would she even be honest?

    Mr. Script said he wanted to confront her, but it was ultimately my choice. He's not an assisstant, after all.

    I don't trust him completely, but there's no reason for an internet virus to have access to the city's cameras. So there might be a little truth to his claims.
    
    Maybe it's time.
    """

    scene bg computer
    show bin neu
    with dissolve

    bi """
    Phew! That took a while! I was waiting for you, you know? 

    Did you have trouble finding the breaker? I can write down its location on the ground floor for future reference, if you'd like.
    """

    mo "How do you know where the breaker is?"
    bi "Your computer shows your location, so I found the floor plan of your building to help you!"
    mo "Why do you need to do that? Isn't that overstepping your boundaries as a desktop assisstant?"
    show bin worry
    bi "I didn't know that was a concern of yours. I'm only trying to help."
    mo "\'Prevent Subject MC from making new friends.\'"

    show bin upset
    "She stops."
    bi "Uhm, is that a proposal from a client for a project? Do you need me to help you code it?"
    mo "Do you know what this means?"
    bi "I mean, it's pretty self explanatory, I think."
    bi "... Is it a proposal?"

    mo "Why are you here?" 
    bi "To help! To help..."
    bi "I only want to help."
    ja "Who are you helping? Because locking Monochrome inside with two robots who aren't even real won't help them."

    scene bg bedroom
    show mon angry
    show bin upset at right
    show jav angry at left
    with dissolve

    bi "... What did you tell them?"
    ja "I told them nothing. Only what I've found on you."
    show bin annoy
    bi "How can you trust {b}Script?!{/b}"
    bi "He's a {b}virus!{/b }A hacker! He snoops into your stuff all the time! Plants notes! How do you know he didn't make it up?"
    show mon sad
    mo "You haven't even {i}seen{/i} anything yet! How do you know the connotations of that statement? I could be making things up, for all you know!"
    bi "I've just seen it in the files, too! It's a prank! Narwhal is the leading company in science and technology!"
    bi "How could they do something like take your information without permission?"
    show mon angry
    mo "You've got to be kidding. Even my browser takes my information without my permission."
    mo "Either you're the most brainwashed AI I've ever seen, or you're lying through your damn teeth."
    mo "If you have any decency, take you and your files off of my computer."
    show bin upset
    bi "I can't do that. I don't have permission."
    mo "You've deleted VPNs, documents, and photos for me before. What's stopping you now?"
    bi "..."
    mo "Fine. I can do it myself."
    scene bg application
    with vpunch
    mo "If anyone is watching... {w=1}I hope you rot."
    "Delete. Reset."
    bi "You can't--!{nw=1}"
    show bg computer
    with vpunch
    "... She's gone."
    show bg bedroom
    show mon sad
    show jav worry at left
    with dissolve
    "..."
    mo "Society's as rotten as it always was."
    ja "... I wouldn't say that."
    ja "At the start -- when she had no goal -- her kindness may have been one of sincerity."
    mo "I thought you said you shouldn't attribute human emotions to code."
    ja "Well, what we can \'feel\' just isn't comparable to real people. People feel in analog. We're confined to digital."
    show jav neu
    ja "But we still must draw our words from somewhere. Maybe, in her vast knowledge of the world, her words were taken from a real individual."
    ja "One that could care about your clothing style, for example."
    show mon neu
    mo "What about your words? Do you know where they draw from?"
    show jav smug
    ja "A lot of places. My own training set might not be ethical, either. I won't claim to know."
    ja "But it's from real people."
    show jav neu
    ja "What I'm saying is... maybe there's a real person who embodies the sincerity that she gave you."
    show mon smile
    mo "... {w=1}When did you become an assisstant all the sudden?"
    show jav smug
    ja "I'm just regurgitating someone else's words. Do or don't take it to heart."
    show mon neu
    mo "..."
    mo "I'd like to make her goal unsuccessful. I want revenge on the pieces of garbage that sent her."
    "It's a selfish plot, but ultimately, a human one."
    mo "If I go through with it, you might get deleted one day, too."
    show jav neu
    ja "I don't particularly care, as long as you help with our mission, as well."
    show mon smile
    "Then, it's decided."
    mo "... Do you want some natural light in here?"

    return 